{"article_id":"1iXDaeeTKKhyB1vd","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The head of the National Security Agency task force","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"assessing the effect of leaks by former NSA contractor Edward Snowden","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"opened the door to the possibility","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"of offering Snowden amnesty in exchange for documents","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"-- though his boss is not on board with the idea .","depth":3},{"id":5,"text":"In an interview with CBS ' `` 60 Minutes , '' Rick Ledgett said","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"that Snowden took `` the keys to the kingdom ''","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"when he left the U.S. earlier this year","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"and was granted temporary asylum in Russia .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"he supports at least having a discussion","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"about offering Snowden amnesty from criminal charges","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"if he returns sensitive files still in his possession ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"and claimed","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"others at the NSA share that view .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"`` My personal view is , yes , it 's worth having a conversation about , ''","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"Ledgett said .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"`` I would need assurances","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"that the remainder of the data could be secured","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"and my bar for those assurances would be very high .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"It would be more than just an assertion on his part . ''","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"However , NSA Director Gen. Keith Alexander sharply disagreed .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"He likened it to `` a hostage taker","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"taking 50 people hostage ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"shooting 10","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"and then say","depth":13},{"id":26,"text":"'You give me full amnesty","depth":14},{"id":27,"text":"and I 'll let the other 40 go . ' ''","depth":14},{"id":28,"text":"`` I think","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"people have to be held accountable for their actions , ''","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"Alexander said .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"`` Because what we do n't want is the next person to do the same thing ,","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"race off to Hong Kong and to Moscow with another set of data","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"knowing","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"they can strike the same deal . '' `","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"` Our position has n't changed on that matter at all , ''","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"Press Secretary Jay Carney said .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"`` What I can tell you is Snowden has been accused of leaking classified information","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"and faces felony charges in the U.S .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"He should be returned to the U.S. as soon as possible","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"where he 'll be afforded due process and protections . ''","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Ledgett also told CBS correspondent John Miller , himself a former employee of the office of the Director of National Intelligence ,","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"that he would not dispute an estimation","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"that Snowden had taken 1.7 million documents from the NSA 's hard drives ,","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"using his security clearance","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"to get around measures","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"that blocked off access for typical employees .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"`` He did something","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"that we call scraping , ''","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Ledgett said .","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"`` Where he went out","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"and just went","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"-- used tools","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"to scrape information from websites ,","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"and put it into a place","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"where he could download it . ''","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"Ledgett said","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"that Snowden had taken `` an exhaustive list of the requirements","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"that have been levied against","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"-- against the National Security Agency .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"And what that gives is , what topics we 're interested in ,","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"where our gaps are .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"But additional information about U.S. capabilities and U.S. gaps is provided as part of that . ''","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"Ledgett estimated","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"that 31,000 of the documents","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"taken by Snowden","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"dealt with U.S. intelligence capabilities and gaps","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"related to countries like China , Russia , and Iran .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"A series of articles","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"published by The Washington Post","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"and by journalist Glenn Greenwald","depth":5},{"id":71,"text":"based on documents","depth":5},{"id":72,"text":"leaked by Snowden","depth":5},{"id":73,"text":"have brought the NSA 's practice","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"of collecting phone records","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"and monitoring Internet use by millions around the world","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"under public scrutiny .","depth":4},{"id":77,"text":"The NSA has consistently defended its practices as legal .","depth":3},{"id":78,"text":"Alexander strongly denied to `` 60 Minutes ''","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"that the NSA could monitor the communications of any American at any time .","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"`` NSA can only target the communications of a U.S. person with a probable cause finding under specific court order , ''","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"Alexander said .","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"`` Today , we have less than 60 authorizations on specific persons","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"to do that . ''","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"Alexander also defended the agency 's practice","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"of collecting so-called `` metadata '' on various phone calls ,","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"including the number","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"dialed , time , date , and frequency .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"`` How do you know","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"when the bad guy","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"who 's using those same communications","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"that my daughters use ,","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"is in the United States","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"trying to do something bad ? ''","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Alexander asked .","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"`` The least intrusive way","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"of doing that","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"is metadata .","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"`` The 'to/from ' number , the duration of the call and date/time , that 's all","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"you get , ''","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"Alexander said later in the interview .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"`` And all","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"we can do","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"is tell the FBI ,","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"'That number is talking to somebody","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"who is very bad ,","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"you ought to go look at it . ' ''","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":213,"left":174,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":111,"right":173,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":111,"left":110,"right":4,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":110,"left":108,"right":109,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":108,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":109,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":114,"right":172,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":114,"left":5,"right":113,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":113,"left":6,"right":112,"relatio